parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission accumulator can cause the vehicle to shake, decelerate, and stall, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes
decelerates
and stalls
especially when stopping during various road conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause loss of brake power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Loss of brake power
overheating of brakes
foreign oil substance in the braking system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause damage to the engine and potentially lead to engine failure, leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Extreme heat in the interior of the vehicle coming from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical/hydraulic brake system can cause loss of brake power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Loss of brake power
failure of the electrical/hydraulic brake system.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Valve and Fuel Pressure Regulator Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle valve and fuel pressure regulator can cause hesitation while accelerating, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Hesitation while accelerating
nearly causing a rear-end collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS sensor can cause the ABS lights to fail, leading to reduced vehicle safety.
symptoms: ABS lights fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk, hesitate, or stall, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission shifts into neutral unexpectedly
the vehicle jerks or hesitates when accelerating
the transmission takes a few minutes to shift into gear
the transmission light and engine light come on
the vehicle feels like it's about to break down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The internal failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, hesitate, or jerk, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission skips or stalls
the RPMs go up when pushing the gas pedal
internal transmission problems
the transmission needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shift mechanism can cause the vehicle to roll when in park, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls when in park
the shift mechanism fails and needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent transmission slippage can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle slips out of gear from park to reverse
the transmission intermittently slips out of gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle rapidly accelerates in reverse gear
loss of brake and steering control
and sudden movement towards the front.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can cause engine damage, engine failure, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil (1-2 quarts every 1000-2000 miles)
engine knocking
and low oil levels without warning lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause accidents, injuries, and strand the driver.
symptoms: Engine failure
engine knocking
and low oil levels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Carbon build-up in engine valves can cause engine failure, excessive oil consumption, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Excessive oil consumption
engine failure
and carbon build-up in engine valves.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight switch can cause the low beam headlights to stop working, leaving only the high beams functional, which can reduce visibility and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The low beam headlights do not turn on
only the high beams work
the headlight switch needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended reduction of power can cause the vehicle to slow down rapidly, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle automatically reduces power
deceleration occurs rapidly
the vehicle loses power while driving
the vehicle stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the acceleration sensor can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to unintended deceleration, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the vehicle decelerates rapidly
the acceleration sensor needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Body and Electrical Harness Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Problems with the throttle body and electrical harness can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to unintended deceleration, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the vehicle decelerates rapidly
the throttle body and electrical harness may need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unwanted acceleration can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially when the vehicle surges forward while the brakes are being applied.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates spontaneously while driving
continues to accelerate or hold a steady speed without depressing the accelerator
requires continuous braking to slow down
revs and then suddenly lurches down when trying to stop
surges when put in gear (forward or reverse)
and may experience rough idling or difficulty starting.
